<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t18320906-432">
               <interp inst="t18320906-432" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18320906-432" type="year" value="1832"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18320906-432" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18320906"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18320906-432" type="date" value="18320906"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18320906-432-off2433-c2527" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-defend3495 t18320906-432-off2433 t18320906-432-verdict2437"></join>
         
               <p>2163. 
               
                  <persName id="t18320906-432-defend3495" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS 
                     STEVENS
                  <interp inst="t18320906-432-defend3495" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-defend3495" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-defend3495" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-defend3495" type="age" value="40"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18320906-432-off2433" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-off2433" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-off2433" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18320906-432-cd2434" type="crimeDate">8th of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-off2433 t18320906-432-cd2434"></join>, 1 truss of hay, value 2s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18320906-432-victim3497" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Richards
                  <interp inst="t18320906-432-victim3497" type="surname" value="Richards"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-victim3497" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-victim3497" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-off2433 t18320906-432-victim3497"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-432-person3498">
                  JAMES 
                  COLE BERRY
               <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3498" type="surname" value="COLE BERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3498" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3498" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a school at <placeName id="t18320906-432-crimeloc2435">Finchley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-432-crimeloc2435" type="placeName" value="Finchley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-432-crimeloc2435" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-off2433 t18320906-432-crimeloc2435"></join>. -On the 8th of September, about half-past two o'clock in the morning, I was at my own door, and heard the footsteps of a man approaching; I took particular notice, and observed that he turned into Mr. Richard's yard - I had just come off a journey, and taken off my shoes to put<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183209060171"></xptr>on another pair, and without saying any thing to my family, I went out, and saw the prisoner with a truss of hay, going from the prosecutor's yard; I followed him, and said he was very early employed that morning - he said he was employed by a gentleman to carry it; I said he should not go any further till he had satisfied me where he got it - he then said he picked it up, and had more right to it than any one, and he would not he stopped by me; I said he should not go any further, and insisted that he should take it back to where he got it from; he, after some time, took it back to Mr. Richards'; I called him up, and kept the prisoner in sight till he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-432-person3499">
                  JAMES 
                  GREGORY
               <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3499" type="surname" value="GREGORY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3499" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3499" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This is Mr. Richards' hay - he is a <rs id="t18320906-432-viclabel2436" type="occupation">farmer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-victim3497 t18320906-432-viclabel2436"></join>; I know it is a truss which I bound on Friday forenoon - it was taken the next morning; I had left it with a load tied for market - the prisoner had worked there formerly, and knew the place.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-432-person3500">
                  JAMES 
                  FROST
               <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3500" type="surname" value="FROST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3500" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-person3500" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was called to take the prisoner - he has lived there for several years.</p>
               <p>JOHN RICHARDS. I had hay of this quality, and have no doubt this is mine.</p>


               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320906-432-verdict2437" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-verdict2437" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 40. - <rs id="t18320906-432-punish2438" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-432-punish2438" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-432-defend3495 t18320906-432-punish2438"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
